In spring 2016 and beginning of summer, pike and lamprey larvae will be released, as well as whitefish in June, summer salmon in July, and pike perches and vimbas in August and September.
The production director of Latvenergo, Maris Kunickis said that care about the environment is one of sustainable development milestones of the holding company Latvenergo.
"When implementing measures of fish stock protection and replenishing, every activity is aimed at environmentally friendly goals, in a close cooperation with the scientific institute Bior for growing fish and releasing them in the Daugava basin as well as implementing other activities," Kunickis pointed out.
More than 600,000 one year old salmon and sea trout smolts will be released in the Daugava estuary this year.
Fish smolts and larvae in scientifically substantiated composition of species are released in the Daugava and its tributaries each year.
In spring 2016, Latvenergo cooperated with the association "Mes zivim" (We for fish) to create 400 artificial fish spawning areas in the Daugava near Kaibala and Ikskile, for the fifth year already.
The cooperation with the association, promoting natural spawning of fish, is an initiative additionally supported by Latvenergo within the framework of fish stock recovery.
The placement of artificial spawning nests in a water-reservoir is an important measure for enhancing fish stock protection and growth in the Daugava.
